  "title": "Resident Technical Officer (C&S)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Resident Technical Officer (Residential Development)</strong></p><p>1. Minimum 5 years’ site experience on residential condominium\nprojects, including ERSS, PBU and precast works.</p><p>2. Experience in inspection and clearance of both structural and\narchitectural finishing works, as well as apartment unit handover from contractor to developer.</p><p>3. Experience in inspecting defect management works during the post-TOP period for condominium projects.</p><p>4. Registered with IES/ACES as an Accredited Resident Technical\nOfficer.</p><p>5. Good knowledge of local authority standards and acceptable\nfinishing tolerances.</p><p>6. Good team player, with the ability to oversee and ensure\ncontractors complete defect rectification within stipulated timelines.<br /><br />7. Preferably with experience in working with marine clay condition and grout mix pile.</p>",
